---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What kind of towel do you use in a sauna?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A large, absorbent cotton or linen towel works best in a sauna. The towel serves two purposes: sitting on it to protect the bench wood from sweat, and drying off after. Turkish towels (peshtemal) are popular for sauna use because they dry fast, stay light when wet, and pack small. Avoid synthetic fabrics — they don't absorb well and can feel uncomfortable against hot skin."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you need a towel in a sauna?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "In most home saunas yes. Sitting directly on the wooden bench without a towel leaves sweat soaked into the wood, which leads to faster degradation and odor over time. In Finnish sauna culture, sitting on a small cotton towel or a pefletti (sauna seat cover) is standard practice. A towel also gives you something to wipe off with when stepping out."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Base
  title="Best Sauna Towels (2025): What to Look For and Top Picks"
  description="What kind of towel works best in a sauna, why you need one, and top picks for home sauna use."
  canonical="/guides/best-sauna-towels"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">Best Sauna Towels (2025)</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-500 mb-8">Updated January 2025 &mdash; Backyard Sauna Pro</p>

    <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
      <img src="/images/lifestyle/sauna-rocks-bucket.jpg" alt="Sauna accessories including towels" class="w-full object-cover max-h-80" loading="lazy" width="1200" height="800" />
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8 text-sm text-stone-700">
      <strong>Affiliate disclosure:</strong> As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases. This page contains affiliate links.
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 mb-4">A sauna towel is one of those things where the wrong choice makes the whole session worse. Synthetic fabrics don't absorb sweat, feel clammy, and can smell bad fast. The right towel makes sitting comfortable, protects the bench wood, and dries quickly between sessions.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Why You Need a Towel in the Sauna</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-6">Two reasons. First, sitting bare on a cedar bench leaves sweat soaking into the wood, which encourages mold and bacteria and shortens the life of the benches. Second, you are going to sweat heavily — having a towel to wipe off before stepping out is basic comfort. In Finnish sauna culture, sitting on a small cotton pefletti (bench towel) is standard etiquette whether at home or at a public sauna.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">What to Look For</h2>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-800 mt-6 mb-2">Material</h3>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">Cotton or linen. Both absorb well, feel good against sweaty skin, and hold up to repeated hot washing. Avoid microfiber and synthetic fabrics — they don't absorb sweat properly and trap heat uncomfortably in a sauna environment.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-800 mt-6 mb-2">Size</h3>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">A standard bath towel (27x52 inches) works well for sitting on and drying off. Some people prefer a larger beach towel to wrap around completely when stepping out into cold air. For bench protection only, a smaller 16x28 hand towel is enough.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-800 mt-6 mb-2">Turkish towels (peshtemal)</h3>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-6">The most popular dedicated sauna towel option. Flat-woven cotton that starts thin and light, absorbs well after a few washes, dries very fast, and doesn't get heavy and musty the way a thick terry cloth towel can. Packs small, easy to store in the sauna anteroom. The tradeoff is less softness compared to plush terry — a preference thing.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-6">Top Picks</h2>

    <div class="space-y-5 mb-10">

      <div class="border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white">
        <div class="mb-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 bg-amber-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wide">Best Overall</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 mt-1">Turkish Cotton Peshtemal Towel</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-3">Flat-woven Turkish cotton, fast-drying, lightweight, absorbs well. The standard choice for dedicated sauna use. Look for 100% cotton and at least 36x70 inches for full wrap coverage. Dozens of options on Amazon — sort by verified reviews and look for ones with cotton composition clearly stated.</p>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=turkish+towel+sauna+peshtemal&tag=backyardsauna-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-block bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-lg transition-colors text-sm">Browse Turkish Sauna Towels</a>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white">
        <div class="mb-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-stone-600 bg-stone-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wide">Bench Cover Option</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 mt-1">Dedicated Sauna Seat Towels</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-3">Smaller cotton or linen bench pads designed specifically for sauna use. Some have a loop to hang on the bench edge so they stay in place. If bench protection is your primary goal rather than a full wrap towel, these are tidier and take up less space.</p>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=sauna+seat+towel+bench&tag=backyardsauna-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-block border border-amber-400 text-amber-700 font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-amber-50 transition-colors">Browse Sauna Bench Towels</a>
      </div>

    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Care and Maintenance</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-6">Wash sauna towels after every session or at least every two sessions. Sweat-soaked towels left sitting develop bacteria and mildew fast. Hot wash is fine for cotton — it helps sanitize. Skip fabric softener, which coats fibers and reduces absorbency over time. Air dry when possible; high heat drying degrades cotton faster than air drying.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">FAQ</h2>
    <div class="space-y-5">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-1">What kind of towel do you use in a sauna?</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-700">Cotton or linen. Turkish towels (peshtemal) are the most popular dedicated option — fast-drying, lightweight, absorb well. Avoid synthetics.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-1">Do you need a towel in a sauna?</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-700">Yes. Sitting on the bench without one soaks sweat into the wood, encouraging mold and bacteria. Standard Finnish sauna etiquette is to always sit on a towel or bench cover.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-6 mt-10">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Related</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li><a href="/guides/best-sauna-accessories" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Best Sauna Accessories</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/sauna-etiquette" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Sauna Etiquette Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/sauna-maintenance-guide" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Sauna Maintenance Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/best-sauna-bucket-ladle" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Best Sauna Bucket and Ladle</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </article>
</Base>
